•   z,y,x : [ z = m.n ∧ y = g.n ∧ x = h.n ∧ a.n < 0
            , y = g.(n+1) ∧ x = h.(n+1) ]
    ⊑
    y,x:= E,F

(1) E = ? // E = (x * a.n) ↑ 1

(2) F = ? // F = (y * a.n) ↑ 1

⊩   Assignment

    •   (y = g.(n+1) ∧ x = h.(n+1))[y,x:= E,F]

    (3) z = m.n
    
    (4) y = g.n
    
    (5) x = h.n
    
    (6) a.n < 0

    ≡   Textual substitution

        E = g.(n+1) ∧ F = h.(n+1)

    ≡   Definitions of g and h, using assumption (6)

        E = (h.n * a.n) ↑ 1 ∧ F = (g.n * a.n) ↑ 1

    ≡   Assumptions (4,5)

        E = (x * a.n) ↑ 1 ∧ F = (y * a.n) ↑ 1

    ■

■